docs.abstract: Campaigns promoting female empowerment are all the rage. But women in advertising say they still have to navigate “Mad Men” workplaces.
docs.snippet: Campaigns promoting female empowerment are all the rage. But women in advertising say they still have to navigate “Mad Men” workplaces.
docs.lead_paragraph: The empowerment of women was a major theme of Advertising Week, a yearly gathering of roughly 100,000 ad-industry people in New York. The female R&B group TLC kicked off the program with a concert called “Future Is Female,” and there were panel discussions with titles like “Mom Bosses,” “#RewriteHerStory” and “Time’s Up, Pay Up: We Will Not Wait 100 Years.”

headline.main: #MeToo Clashes With ‘Bro Culture’ at Ad Agencies

docs.abstract: More details about the former auto executive’s escape emerged. The Japanese news media said cameras showed him leaving his Tokyo home alone.

docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Carlos Ghosn was aided in his escape from Japan by an American security consultant who accompanied him on the flight out of the country, a person familiar with the matter said, while a Turkish charter jet company said on Friday that its planes were used illegally to pull off the plan.
